ProtoDefines:
. "We call the natural reduction map $\mathbf{Z} \to 
   \Z/n\Z{}$, which sends $a$ to $a+n\mathbf{Z}$, \term{ 
   reduction modulo} $n$. We also say that $a$ is a \term{lift}
   of $a+n\mathbf{Z}$. Thus, e.g., $7$ is a lift of $1$ mod 
   $3$, since $7+3\mathbf{Z} = 1+3\mathbf{Z}$."
